  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Patients will be selected from the Center for Parkinson's disease of the IRCCS Neuromed,
        according to specific inclusion criteria. Approximatey 500 subjects, 30 years of age or
        older, recruited with a family-based approach, will be included in the study.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of at least two out the following cardinal signs: resting tremor, cogwheel
             rigidity, bradykinesia, asymmetrical onset of symptoms and symptomatic response to
             L-dopa (levodopa)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Previous thalamotomy on the implanted sided, significant brain atrophy or structural
             damage seen on CT or MRI, marked cognitive dysfunction, active psychiatric symptoms,
             or concurrent neurological or other uncontrolled medical disorders.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
